    <div class="AssessmentProblem.identifier">102784</div>
    <div class="AssessmentProblem.type">RestrictedConstructedResponse</div>
    <div class="AssessmentProblem.statement"><p>In a smoothie recipe, the ratio of cups of milk and cups of frozen berries is <span class="math math-repaired" data-png-file-id="6194">\(4:3\)</span>. For each question, explain your reasoning.</p>

<ol>
	<li>To make&#xA0;14 cups of the smoothie, how many cups of milk are needed?</li>
	<li>To make 28 cups of the smoothie, how many cups of frozen berries are needed?</li>
</ol>
</div>
    <div class="AssessmentProblem.solution"><ol>
	<li>8 cups, because there are 7 units, so each unit is worth 2 cups.<span class="math math-repaired" data-png-file-id="45320">\(14\div7=2\)</span> and <span class="math math-repaired" data-png-file-id="45361">\(2\boldcdot 4=8\)</span>.</li>
	<li>12 cups, because <span class="math math-repaired" data-png-file-id="40876">\(28\div7=4\)</span>, so each unit is worth 4 cups. <span class="math math-repaired" data-png-file-id="45415">\(4\boldcdot 3=12\)</span>.</li>
</ol>
</div>
